課程教材 Course Material
Required Texts
Veenema, T. G. (2013). Disaster nursing and emergency preparedness for chemical, biological, and radiological terrorism and other hazards (3rd ed.). New York: Springer Pub. Co. 
Recommended Texts
Adelman, D., & Legg, T. (2009). Disaster nursing: A handbook for practice. Massachusetts: Jones & Bartlett Learning.
Akins, R.B., Williams, J. R., Silenas, R. & Edwards, J. C. (2005). The role of public health nurses in bioterrorism preparedness. Disaster Management & Response, 3 (4), 98-105.
Davies, K. (2005). Disaster preparedness and response: More than major incidence initiation. British Journal of Nursing, 14(16), 868-871.
Fung, W. M. O., Lai, K.Y. C & Loke, A. Y. (2009). Nurses’ perception of disaster: Implications for disaster nursing curriculum. Journal of Clinical Nursing, 18(22),  3165-3171.
Langan, J.C. (2005). Preparing nurses for disaster management. New Jersey: Pearson.
Powers, R., & Daily, E. (2010). International Disaster Nursing: Cambridge University Press.
Wall, B. M., & Kelling A. W. (2010).  Nurses on the front line: when disaster strikes, 1878-2010. New York: Springer Publishing.
Wise, G. I. (2007). Preparing for disaster: A way of developing community relationships. Disaster Management & Response, 5 (1), 14-17.
Useful web sites
International Strategy for Disaster Reduction (ISDR) (2010). World disaster reduction campaign 2010-2011. Retrieved from http://www.unisdr.org/english/campaigns/campaign2010-2011/
World Health Organization (WHO) and International Council of Nurses (ICN) (2009). ICN Framework of disaster nursing competencies. Retrieved from http://www.icn.ch/images/stories/documents/networks/DisasterPreparednessNetwork/Disaster_Nursing_Competencies_lite.pdf
World Society of Disaster Nursing (2008). World society of disaster nursing established. Retrieved from http://www.wsdn2008.com/index.html

     

