課程概述 Course Description
       This course introduces the concepts of disasters and disaster mitigation, and the importance and function of disaster nursing. Emergency care of physical and psychological injury caused by nature or man-made disaster as well as disaster management and prevention at different phases of disaster will be discussed. Major topics include disaster assessment, emergency management, disaster triage, care provision for victims, establishment of emergent service system and informatics sharing system, self-care, and disaster preparedness will be covered in this course.
This course introduces the concepts of disasters and disaster mitigation, and the importance and function of disaster nursing. Emergency care of physical and psychological injury caused by nature or man-made disaster as well as disaster management and prevention at different phases of disaster will be discussed. Major topics include disaster assessment, emergency management, disaster triage, care provision for victims, establishment of emergent service system and informatics sharing system, self-care, and disaster preparedness will be covered in this course.

    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
Define and describe the concepts of disaster nursing.Outline the basic principles of emergency management.Identify preparation for disaster in a communityIdentify nursing activities during and after disasterDescribe the process in rebuilding the communities after disasterApply finding of disaster research to suggest nursing care for vulnerable groupDevelop a plan for a patient experiencing psychological effects after a disaster 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Introduction of course & syllabus/ 
Introduction of disaster and disaster nursing2Disaster preparedness3Overview of disaster management4Infection control and health promotion in disaster5Types of disaster and special care  or  Disaster triage6Visit institutions (I)7Types of disaster and Special care8Ethical and legal issues in disaster9Midterm group presentations  (case analysis and management activities) 10Visit institutions (II)11Nursing roles and function in disaster 12Gender issues and vulnerable population in disaster 13Multidisciplinary crisis management and risk communication14Media and communication 15Visit institutions (III)16Understanding and management the psychosocial impact of disasters17Group Presentation18Group presentation and course  evaluation 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


